{{Multiple issues| {{Notability|Academics|date=January 2015}} {{BLP sources|date=May 2016}}}} '''Josef Strobl''' is an Austrian [[geographer]]. He is a professor at the [[University of Salzburg]] and leads its Centre for Geoinformatics and the GIScience Institute. Strobl was key to the implementation of the worldwide [[UNIGIS]] postgraduate distance learning programme. He leads the annual [[AGIT]] and [[GI Forum (symposium)|GI_Forum]] symposia in Salzburg.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dk-giscience.zgis.net/index.php/team/faculty/josef-strobl |title=Archived copy |accessdate=October 26, 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141026121226/http://dk-giscience.zgis.net/index.php/team/faculty/josef-strobl |archivedate=October 26, 2014 }}</ref>
==Education== *Habilitation, Geography, [[University of Salzburg]], Salzburg, Austria, 1993 *Doctor of Science (Dr.rer.nat.), Geography, [[University of Vienna]], Austria, 1984 *Master of Science (Mag.rer.nat.), Geography, [[University of Vienna]], Austria, 1982<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jstrobl.zgis.net/|title=Josef Strobl|website=Jstrobl.zgis.net|accessdate=12 May 2016}}</ref>
