{{Use Australian English|date=February 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}} {{kml}} This is a '''list of active [[power stations]] in [[Tasmania]], [[Australia]]'''. Candidates for this list must already be commissioned and capable of generating {{convert|1|MW|sing=on}} or more of [[electricity]].
== Gas == === Thermal gas === These power stations use gas combustion to power [[steam turbines]] that [[Electricity generation|generate]] some or all of the [[electricity]] they produce.
{| class="wikitable sortable" style="text-align: center" ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Power station ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Coordinates ! scope="col" colspan=2| [[Electric power|Max. capacity]] ! scope="col" rowspan=2| [[Steam turbine|Turbines]] ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Fuel type ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Ref. |- ! scope="col" | [[Megawatt|MW]] ! scope="col" | [[Horsepower|hp]] |- | align="left" | [[Bell Bay Power Station|Bell Bay]] | {{coord|41|8|31|S|146|54|9|E|name=Bell Bay Power Station}} | {{Convert|240|MW|hp|0|disp=table}} | 2 | [[Natural gas]] | |}
=== Gas turbine === These [[gas turbine]] power stations use gas combustion to generate some or all of the electricity they produce.
{| class="wikitable sortable" style="text-align: center" ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Power station ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Coordinates ! scope="col" colspan=2| [[Electric power|Max. capacity]] ! scope="col" rowspan=2| [[Steam turbine|Turbines]] ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Fuel type ! scope="col" rowspan=2| [[Combined cycle]] ! scope="col" rowspan=2| Ref. |- ! scope="col" | [[Megawatt|MW]] ! scope="col" | [[Horsepower|hp]] |- | align="left" | [[Bell Bay Power Station|Bell Bay]] | {{coord|41|8|31|S|146|54|9|E|name=Bell Bay Power Station}} | {{convert|135|MW|hp|0|disp=table}} | 3 | Natural gas | No | |- | align="left" | [[AETV_Power_Station|Tamar Valley]] | | {{convert|210|MW|hp|0|disp=table}} | 5 | Natural gas | Yes | |}
Note that the above three power stations are in fact the same power station listed upon commissioning after conversion to gas and recommissioning after a turbine upgrade. It has been decommissioned since 2009.
