'''Markaz''' is an [[Arabic language|Arabic]] term meaning "center."  In the Middle East, the word (or a [[Persian language|Persian]] and [[Turkish language|Turkish]] derivative) is sometimes used for second-level [[country subdivision]]s.  Among these are:

* [[Markazes of Egypt]]
* Markaz in Saudi Arabia, below [[Governorates of Saudi Arabia]]
* The [[capital city]] of a [[Provinces of Iran|province]] of [[Iran]]
* In [[Turkey]], a merkez is a [[districts of Turkey|district]] (ilçe) that serves as the capital of a province.

